Total Sells 810 U.K. Gas Stations to Rontec for $600 Million

-- B y   W i l l   K e n n e d y   a n d   T a r a   P a t e l
-- 
2011-06-21T17:36:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/total-sells-810-u-k-gas-stations-to-rontec-for-600-million-1-.html
Total SA (FP)  sold its U.K. network of
810 service stations to Rontec Investments LLP for about $600
million as part of a strategy to scale back its European
refining and retail operations.  Rontec, a group led by Snax 24, will sell 254 of the sites
to  Royal Dutch Shell Plc (RDSA)  for $400 million in cash, Shell said in
a statement. Those stations will be managed by Snax 24.  The Rontec group includes investment firm Grovepoint and
asset manager Investec, Total said in a statement. The Rontec
sale was worth around $600 million, according to Michael
Crochet-Vourey, a spokesman for Total.  The process of selling Totalâ€™s U.K. Lindsey refinery is
ongoing, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
